<br>
You have to remember something.  What level is this spell?  What level are the monsters that use that area as a crossroads?  Evacs are supposed to get you OUT of danger, that's why there isn't a Cazic Thule evac.<br>
<br>
&lt;&lt;Concussion was said to be level 39 because it helps regaining concentration when you cast a spell at least 10 levels below your current level, not because of fizzles. This is obviously important for a spell like concussion, which is meant to be cast when you're being beaten on.&gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
Another interesting rumor, but channelling gives you a chance to recover to cast A spell, not specific spells.  Regaining concentration is only based on channeling, the skill, no other factors.  The reason you can tend to cast lower level spells with channeling at higher level is because.... they are quicker in the past than your most recent spells until level 51.<br>
<br>
Sorry, that isn't the reason either.  You want to know the reason, from GZ, what Verant actually said, not rumors and speculation?<br>
<br>
&quot;Just because a spell is at a given level doesn't mean it is supposed to be used then.&quot;<br>
<br>
